                            <comment id="13295500" author="davsclaus" created="Fri, 15 Jun 2012 07:16:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Can you try with latest Camel releases as we say on the support page&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;http://camel.apache.org/support&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://camel.apache.org/support&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Also what are the exact HTTP header / body you send to the Camel jetty endpoint? The HTTP headers need to indiciate its binary data.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13295558" author="metatech" created="Fri, 15 Jun 2012 09:53:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Claus,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I created the following route :&lt;br/&gt;
        &amp;lt;route id=&quot;proxy-console&quot;&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
            &amp;lt;from uri=&quot;jetty:&lt;a href=&quot;http://0.0.0.0:9007/console/system/console?matchOnUriPrefix=true&amp;amp;chunked=true&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://0.0.0.0:9007/console/system/console?matchOnUriPrefix=true&amp;amp;amp;chunked=true&lt;/a&gt;&quot;/&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
            &amp;lt;to uri=&quot;jetty:&lt;a href=&quot;http://localhost:8181/system/console?bridgeEndpoint=true&amp;amp;throwExceptionOnFailure=false&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://localhost:8181/system/console?bridgeEndpoint=true&amp;amp;amp;throwExceptionOnFailure=false&lt;/a&gt;&quot;/&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
        &amp;lt;/route&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;And I call the following URL :&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;http://localhost:9007/console/system/console/res/flags/en.gif&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://localhost:9007/console/system/console/res/flags/en.gif&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
which is corrupted.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The content-type is &quot;image/gif&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-5274&quot; title=&quot;Jetty client can corrupt streams if used in a bridge mode (proxy)&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CAMEL-5274&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CAMEL-5274&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; is probably the same problem.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13295574" author="davsclaus" created="Fri, 15 Jun 2012 10:31:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Can you try with chunked=false&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13295594" author="metatech" created="Fri, 15 Jun 2012 11:21:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The original file (via direct URL) is 367 bytes.&lt;br/&gt;
With a camel-jetty proxy :&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;chunked=false -&amp;gt; 358 bytes (1 character set conversion only)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;chunked=true -&amp;gt; 658 bytes (2 character set conversions)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="13395896" author="davsclaus" created="Mon, 18 Jun 2012 13:55:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Now fixed when chunked=false as well.&lt;br/&gt;
This together with &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-5274&quot; title=&quot;Jetty client can corrupt streams if used in a bridge mode (proxy)&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CAMEL-5274&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CAMEL-5274&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; fixes this all together.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
